= Text

Text styling.

The #link("/docs/reference/text/text/")[text function] is of particular interest.

== Definitions

- #link("/docs/reference/text/highlight/")[highlight]Highlights text with a background color.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/linebreak/")[linebreak]Inserts a line break.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/lorem/")[lorem]Creates blind text.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/lower/")[lower]Converts a string or content to lowercase.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/overline/")[overline]Adds a line over text.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/raw/")[raw]Raw text with optional syntax highlighting.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/smallcaps/")[smallcaps]Displays text in small capitals.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/smartquote/")[smartquote]A language-aware quote that reacts to its context.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/strike/")[strike]Strikes through text.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/sub/")[sub]Renders text in subscript.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/super/")[super]Renders text in superscript.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/text/")[text]Customizes the look and layout of text in a variety of ways.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/underline/")[underline]Underlines text.
- #link("/docs/reference/text/upper/")[upper]Converts a string or content to uppercase.
